ExoSkeleton PHP 5.3 Framework

Features:
- Routing definition and loading
- Environment definition and loading
- Clean response methods
- Basic templating inclusion
- Entity passthrough class for property definition

Coming Soon:
- Database interface classes extending PDO
- RESTful application interfacing

(Maybe) Coming Soon Via Other Projects:
- Existence PHP ORM
- ExoTest Unit Testing Framework
- ExoUI Form/UI Toolkit

HOW-TO USE:
- Add route to app/config/routes.php:

	Route::add('example', array(
		'pattern' => '/example',
		'class' => 'Example\Application',
		'method' => 'hello_world'
	));

- Create a new class in app/modules/Example/Application.php

	/**
	 * Example Application
	 * @author Guillaume VanderEst <guillaume@vanderest.org>
	 */
	namespace Example;
	class Application Extends \Exo\Application
	{
		public function hello_world()
		{
			return 'Hello World';
		}
	}
